g of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnès Nanteuil was born in 1105, her father, Théobald DE CREPY II, was 30 and her mother, Elisabeth Gauthier DE CHÂTILLON, was 30. She married Guillaume de Garlande III Anseau in 1125, in Ivry-la-Bataille, Eure, Upper Normandy, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died about 1180, at the age of 76."},"et":{"1105–environ 1180":"1105–umbes 1180","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1104–1117":"1104–1117","1100–1132":"1100–1132","–1117":"–1117","–1177":"–1177","1125–1191":"1125–1191","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Surnud","após 1177":"pärast 1177","1132":"1132","1141":"1141","1075":"1075","1140":"1140","environ 1180":"umbes 1180","1095":"1095","1191":"1191","1180":"1180","1117":"1117","1105":"1105","after 1117":"pärast 1117","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","1100":"1100","about 1130":"umbes 1130","Nanteuil-Le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Europa":"Europe","Ivry-La-Bataille, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France":"Ivry-la-Bataille, Eure, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1105–environ 1180":"1105–noin 1180","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1104–1117":"1104–1117","1100–1132":"1100–1132","–1117":"–1117","–1177":"–1177","1125–1191":"1125–1191","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Kuollut","após 1177":"1177 jälkeen","1132":"1132","1141":"1141","1075":"1075","1140":"1140","environ 1180":"noin 1180","1095":"1095","1191":"1191","1180":"1180","1117":"1117","1105":"1105","after 1117":"1117 jälkeen","1104":"1104","1125":"11